    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/REN24/pages/21758484\" rel=\"nofollow\">Aggregate volumes</a> are a new technique allowing you to render overlapping volumes more efficiently and lower the time to first pixel. It also allows PxrSurface to use a heterogeneous volume in its interior integrator.</p><p>Aggregates rendering requires a specific setup in maya.</p><h2 id=\"AggregateVolumesinMaya-AggregateMembership\">Aggregate Membership</h2><p>All renderable volumetric primitives must be in the same rmanVolumeAggregateSet set. This node works as a regular maya set and a <strong>globalVolumeAggregate </strong>set is created in every new scene.</p><p>The set should contain the shapes, NOT the transforms.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"b9511c08-98a5-40a3-87cb-06677b304abf\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Any volumetric primitive <strong>not</strong> included in the integrator's set will be <strong>not render.</strong></p></div></div><h2 id=\"AggregateVolumesinMaya-IntegratorSettings\">Integrator Settings</h2><p>PxrPathTracer support volume aggregates, starting with RenderMan 24.2.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"496\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/PxrPathTracer_24_2_aggregate_settings.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=496&amp;height=464\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544540118/PxrPathTracer_24_2_aggregate_settings.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"864\" data-width=\"922\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544540138\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"PxrPathTracer_24_2_aggregate_settings.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544540118\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"a85250ad-a304-4a04-8ceb-521090e392cd\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/PxrPathTracer_24_2_aggregate_settings.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=922&amp;height=864 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/PxrPathTracer_24_2_aggregate_settings.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=496&amp;height=464 1x\"></span><p>Once you have added all the volumes to your <strong>globalVolumeAggregate </strong>set, enter the name of the set in PxrPathTracer's <strong>Volume Aggregate Name</strong>.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"dcdfc941-66a2-4d19-8977-857e5cd50ed3\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>If the name field is left empty, the old volume rendering method will be used.</p></div></div><p>Volume aggregates are faster because they ignore the classic visibility settings (camera, transmission, indirect). If you need to override one or more visibility flags, you must:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Create a new rmanVolumeAggregateSet node per override containing the volumes that should be visible.</p></li><li><p>Enter that set name in the corresponding field of PxrPathTracer:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Camera Aggregate Override: a set of volumes visible to camera rays</p></li><li><p>Indirect Aggregate Override: a set of volumes visible to indirect rays</p></li><li><p>Transmission Aggregate Override: a set of volumes visible to transmission rays</p></li></ol></li></ol><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"0e7faaa9-cc28-419a-be24-3a7cbb345831\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>The same set name can be used in multiple visibility fields</p></div></div><p><strong>Joint Sampling</strong>: enables importance sampling of visibility and light sources. This is beneficial when lights are near a thin volume or when thin volume is lit by a distant light. Joint sampling has a cost and should be disabled when not required.</p><h2 id=\"AggregateVolumesinMaya-Nodeparameters\">Node parameters</h2><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"530\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volume_params.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=398\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volume_params.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"682\" data-width=\"908\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544540135\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"24.2_aggregate_volume_params.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544540118\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"552af0e1-88c6-4bdb-acc6-a3cd7ecbf1a3\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volume_params.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=908&amp;height=682 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volume_params.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=398 1x\"></span><p><strong>Aggregate Membership</strong>: shows which aggregate the current node belongs to. You can use the side menu to modify the membership.</p><p><strong>DSO Min/Max</strong>: When enabled, procedural nodes (like openVDB) will build a spatial acceleration structure to speed up rendering.</p><p>The following parameters are only supported on openVDB volumes:</p><p style=\"margin-left: 30.0px;\"><strong>Filter Width</strong>: Volume aggregates use a form of volume mip-mapping that allows you to bias the optimal level of detail.</p><p style=\"margin-left: 30.0px;\"><strong>Density Scale</strong>: Scale the density on the fly, as the volume data in loaded by the renderer.</p><p style=\"margin-left: 30.0px;\"><strong>Density Rolloff</strong>: Remap density to make less dense areas wispier or denser.</p><h2 id=\"AggregateVolumesinMaya-PxrSurfaceInteriorAggregateVolume\">PxrSurface Interior Aggregate Volume</h2><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"530\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volumes_pxrsurface.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=145\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volumes_pxrsurface.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"244\" data-width=\"890\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544540132\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"24.2_aggregate_volumes_pxrsurface.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544540118\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"515076a6-584f-4524-96fe-874ec17d2a62\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volumes_pxrsurface.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=890&amp;height=244 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544540118/24.2_aggregate_volumes_pxrsurface.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431553384&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=530&amp;height=145 1x\"></span><p>PxrSurface allows you to bind an aggregate volume set to its interior integrator, to render cloudy water, gemstones, etc.</p><p />"
    }
  },
